HEADWORD: Nitrite
<hw>Ni"trite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>nitrite</ets>. See <er>Niter</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
salt or ester of nitrous acid; a compound bearing the
<chform>-NO2</chform> radical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Amyl nitrite</b></col>, <cd>a yellow oily volatile
liquid, used in medicine as a depressant and a vaso-dilator. Its
inhalation produces an instantaneous flushing of the face.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nitro</ent>⟦br⟧
